labels.value: Climate Corps is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. Please note that this section of the application is voluntary and your responses will be fully confidential. Providing us information about your identity will allow us to track the effectiveness of our recruiting and DEI efforts and ensure that the needs of all fellows are taken into consideration.

You may address your cover letter to the Climate Corps Team. Please describe any specific courses, qualifications, skills and experience (academic, professional, or personal) that have prepared you for the Climate Corps fellowship. Finally, please describe how a Climate Corps fellowship will impact your career.
Thank you for your interest in applying to Climate Corps. Please fill out the information below.
It looks like this email is already tied to an active account, please reset your password instead.

Please select the top 5 projects for which you would like to be considered. To do so, select your preferred projects by opening the project description and using the arrows to adjust the rank (1-5, 1 being your top choice). In the comment box, write a paragraph (approximately 5 sentences) stating your case for each of those projects.

Be sure to reference prior work experiences and academic training that are relevant to each organization’s project description. Many projects will indicate required or additional skillset that are pertinent to the fellow’s role; please consider these as you make your selections. Remember, this is your opportunity to tell us why you’re the best choice for this project! The more detailed information you provide, the easier it will be for our matching team to place you with the placement that best aligns with your interests and skillset. Please be sure to read all of the logistical considerations for projects to ensure they are a good match for your needs.

Projects with gold starts are particularly competitive placements. Projects with blue stars are those that we would like to highlight for your consideration.

If there are projects outside of your top 5 that you would like to be considered for, use the bookmark symbol to indicate interest.

You can save your work at any time using the Save All button, which allows you to come back to it later. Once you Submit, you will no longer be able to make changes to your selections or comments.

EDF does not guarantee placement with any one organization. If you do not enter any host preferences, you will not be considered for a placement.

• .If you prefer on-site vs. remote fellowships, use the “Fellowship Location Preference” filter. Be sure to also look at projects marked as Fellow Preference, as those hosts have indicated they are open to on-site or remote arrangements.

• .On-site projects that are not accessible by public transportation will require a private vehicle. If you don’t have access to a private vehicle, filter for remote projects OR projects that are accessible by public transportation.
• .Make use of the search bar, particularly if you’re looking for projects outside our main project types.
• .Projects without a fellowship city or state have multiple location options, so try using the search bar if you’re not seeing projects in the state you are looking for.
